You all have absolutely no "You all have absolutely no "You all have absolutely no "You all have absolutely no spine""" reacts only #MetaEveryThingAgain

You all have absolutely no spines.Your collection of human vertebrae pales in comparison to mine. Not to mention incredibly hypocritical. I took the hypocritic oath and apparently that's not the one doctors take but that won't stop me from my back alley vertebrae harvesting enterprise. That's why you'll never succeed in life. Sure, you all can turn in essays, or be deemed not-guilty by a jury of your peers (congrats, so can the rest of us once we threaten to steal their spines. No one cares). But you have no conflict resolution or meme creating skills outside of "It's Quaker Days" Or "OH GOOD LORD I'M IN SO MUCH PAIN I CANNOT SUPPORT MY OWN BODY WEIGHT WITHOUT MY SACRUM OF COCCYX" as you slump to the ground, demanding that some higher authority remove any unpleasant feelings by injecting you with Chocolate Rain. It's actually quite sad. Many of you have the potential to accomplish great memes in this life. But evidently, you'll never get out of your own way, or allow your skeleton to leave your body. I'm sorry, but if you can't handle the fact that there is a skeleton inside you, or citations from the university because your memes are too dank, or the current Cheeto who pilots the the United States, or the mere existence of someone with a 1200 rare pepe collection, you're never going to successfully navigate life outside of the "safe space" of NOT using the deep web behind 7 proxies. 
What are some of you actually thinking? No really, I want to know; harvesting spines has been lucrative, but I want to weigh my options before I consider pilfering brains. That you can somehow meme and complain your way to becoming an admin on OUPSCC because some guys or grills on Columbia Buy Sell shared memes or jokes about things you'll see on 4chan? You can't be serious?.. Get over yourselves! You're in the easiest situation of your entire lives, too late to explore the world, too early to explore space, and you're already throwing in the towel over Internet memes!? After your 4 years here, no one is going to want to deal with your sanctimonious and disingenuous Locust Walk memes. I honestly don't care if you don't not refuse to reject your null hypothesis of not believing me. Because you will absolutely find out the hard way after a month into your job when you start making the same kinds of memes. They're not going to cater to your bandwagon nostalgia farming (member Star Wars?)
I really want to be wrong. Because like I said above, you're all incredibly talented and capable individuals, with strong yet malleable backbones, who have so much to offer the skeleton war. I want to see you all go on to accomplishing great things in government, Reddit, Clickhole, the bulletin board of your local YMCA, or the orphanage you have a restraining order from because you wanted "smaller spines". So please, channel your time and energy into developing the mental fortitude that will solve the REAL meme deficiencies of this world. Because internet memes about Spring Fling will not, nor will it ever be, a real and serious channeling of dark existential humor.
Please feel free to message me if you have any remixes or YoutubePoops about what I had to say. Unless it's "Has Anyone Really Been Far Even as Decided to Use Even Go Want to do Look More Like?" Then I can assure I'll post the navy seal copypasta.
